Class Boundary

  • java.lang.Object
    • Boundary

  • public class Boundary
extends java.lang.Object
    A boundary consists of:
    • a top path as a list of points.
    • a bottom path as a list of points.
    Points are represented as integers. Invariant: The top and bottom paths should have common end-points, called anchors.
